refentry.refsect1:
&ref.title.note;
This task require PECL's Phar extension to be installed on your system.
Phar is built-in in PHP from 5.3 version.

&ref.title.attributes;


  Attributes for PharPackageTask

  &taskAttributes.table.titlesLine.all;



    basedir

    String

    Base directory, which will be deleted from
    each included file (from path). Paths with deleted
    basedir part are local paths in package.

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.yes;




    destfile

    String

    Destination (output) file. Will be recreated,
    if exists!

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.yes;




    compression

    String

    Compression type (gzip,
    bzip2, none) to apply to the packed
    files.

    none

    &attributes.required.no;




    webstub

    String

    Relative path within the phar package to run,
    if accessed through a web browser.

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.no;




    clistub

    String

    Relative path within the phar package to run,
    if accessed on the command line.

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.no;




    stub

    String

    A path to a php file that contains a custom
    stub

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.no;




    alias

    String

    An alias to assign to the phar package

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.no;




    signature

    String

    Signature algorithm (md5,
    sha1, sha256, sha512), used for
    this package.

    sha1

    &attributes.required.no;

&ref.title.example;
Sample build command:
<pharpackage destfile="./build/package.phar" basedir="./"> <fileset dir="./classes"> <include name="**/**" /> </fileset> <metadata> <element name="version" value="1.0" /> <element name="authors"> <element name="John Doe"> <element name="e-mail" value="john@example.com" /> </element> </element> </metadata> </pharpackage>
